        <definition>void amrex::Gpu::TrackedVector&lt; T &gt;::release_gpu</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>release_gpu</name>
        <qualifiedname>amrex::Gpu::TrackedVector::release_gpu</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Release GPU memory</para>
<para>If the device side was modified (device_dirty), syncs device data back to the host first so no updates are lost. Host data preserved for reuse until destructor. This enables use outside of and across <ref refid="classamrex_1_1AMReX" kindref="compound">AMReX</ref> init/finalize cycles. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
